1. November 27th, truly an amazing ending to otherwise a mid-to-shitty year. @Universe Janitor reminded me that LPDP has announced the results, and I was far from optimistic. But lo and behold

2. July, I was offered a part-time job as a nutritionist in my old school, which I gladly accepted since prior to that, all I did was endlessly looking for a master degree scholarship while my mates were all continuing their education to be doctors and dietitians

3. December 12th, my half sister's wedding, which coincided with my birthday and my stepmom's birthday

4. June, with a heavy heart I had to break up with my ex for many reasons, one of which was preparing for LPDP (she can't handle LDR). But looking back in retrospect, it goes to show that I can love deeply

5. August, when I went to visit the aftermath of a protest and was threatened to be arrested for taking photos while talking on VC. That was exhilarating oh my

Author: floatingtales
Content:
Wrapped 2025 -

5. September - Somehow snuck my way to moderating G-Space, gotten *real* inside scoops on indonesian politics.

4. February - First time going to Europe (England/Wales), cold af. Apparently in Wales, the f-word slur for homosexuals are actually sausage meatballs in that area.

3. October - Sent my mom to go on to her pilgrimage trip to the Vatican for the year of the Jubilee, given her some pocket money too, she brought lots of chocolate back. Also the time I went to Taipei with dad and bro since covid.

2. March-August - Got to pay to have house fixed after it's been laid off for a while, shit's been falling apart for a while, and I've only got enough salary to pay for 2 tukangs weekly, so it's been dragging on for a while. Also, apparently there's *a lot of things to be fixed*

1. December - Time of reflection. This year, I've been spending a lot of money, but tbh, almost everything is for a good cause. *I'm broke*, but love that my money has been used for good.

Author: dusman05
Content:
1. June: Happy to be done with College and graduate. After nearly 4 years of hard work, I finally received my Bachelor‚Äôs. At that time my future was still very uncertain on what will happen and what I will do, but I will figure it out along the way. Family came over to visit for the ceremony and had a nice vacation with them.

2. September: Finally some certainty on my future and I got my first job offer out of college which was such a painstaking process, It‚Äôs been tough for International students and the Job market has been rough right now. Thankful that I could even get one, let alone one of the roles I actually had on the top of my list.

3. November: Just had to be it. Ran a great Half Marathon which could put me in solid contention in the future among Indonesian elite runners, good to know that I can punch up above my weight and that I‚Äôm one step closer to competing at the elite level.

4. July: Did a lot of hiking, soul searching in the forests and mountains. Unsure of where and what I would go/do at that moment and being in nature takes a lot off my mind. Got to admire a lot of God‚Äôs beautiful creation on this Earth and how blessed we are to live in it.

5. December: Bittersweet month really. Said goodbye to a lot of friends because they were going back to Indo or getting job offers elsewhere, but it reminded me again that people around you won‚Äôt be there forever so spend quality time with them and cherish the moments you shared together, even when we will be far apart I would make extra effort to stay in touch with them.
